
```markdown
# 🎓 AtomcCamp Smart LMS 

## Problem Statement

Traditional Learning Management Systems (LMS) offer a one‑size‑fits‑all experience. Learners with different backgrounds, goals, and available study time often struggle to find the right course or stay motivated. Instructors lack real‑time insights into student progress and struggle to identify at‑risk learners early. There is no intelligent, adaptive system that personalises learning paths and provides AI‑powered assistance inside the course.

**atomcamp Smart LMS** solves this by using **Claude AI** to:
- Assess each learner’s profile (background, programming level, goals, commitment, domain interest)
- Recommend the most suitable course and a secondary path
- Provide an **AI study assistant (AtomBot)** inside every lesson
- Give instructors a dashboard with risk analytics and AI‑generated intervention plans

---

## Features

- 🤖 **AI Skill Assessment** – 5 adaptive questions analysed by Claude.
- 🎯 **Personalised Course Recommendations** – primary & secondary courses with match score.
- 📊 **Student Dashboard** – progress tracking, weekly activity, skill radar, AI insights.
- 💬 **AtomBot Chat** – AI study assistant (Claude) embedded in each course.
- 👩‍🏫 **Instructor Dashboard** – student progress overview, at‑risk list, one‑click AI intervention plan.
- 🔐 **Secure API Proxy** – Anthropic API key never exposed to the browser.

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer          | Technology |
|----------------|------------|
| Frontend       | React 18, Vite, CSS‑in‑JS |
| Backend (local)| Node.js, Express |
| Backend (prod) | Vercel Serverless Functions |
| AI             | Anthropic Claude API |
| Deployment     | Vercel (frontend + serverless) |
| Version Control| Git + GitHub |

---

## Steps to Run the Project

### Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+
- Anthropic API key – [Get one here](https://console.anthropic.com/)

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/HaiderAli-Awan/atomcamp-lms.git
cd atomcamp-lms
```

### 2. Install frontend dependencies
```bash
cd frontend
npm install
```

### 3. Set up the local backend (proxy)
From the project root:
```bash
mkdir backend
cd backend
npm init -y
npm install express cors dotenv
npm install -D nodemon
```

Create `backend/server.js`:
```javascript
import express from "express";
import cors from "cors";
import dotenv from "dotenv";

dotenv.config();
const app = express();
app.use(cors());
app.use(express.json());

const ANTHROPIC_API_KEY = process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY;

app.post("/api/claude", async (req, res) => {
  const { messages, system } = req.body;
  const response = await fetch("https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages", {
    method: "POST",
    headers: {
      "Content-Type": "application/json",
      "x-api-key": ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,
      "anthropic-version": "2023-06-01",
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      model: "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022",
      max_tokens: 1000,
      messages,
      system: system || "",
    }),
  });
  const data = await response.json();
  res.json({ content: data.content[0].text });
});

const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3001;
app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Backend on port ${PORT}`));
```

Create `backend/.env`:
```
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_actual_api_key_here
PORT=3001
```

### 4. Run both servers

**Terminal 1 – Backend**
```bash
cd backend
npm run dev   # runs on http://localhost:3001
```

**Terminal 2 – Frontend**
```bash
cd frontend
npm run dev   # runs on http://localhost:5173
```

Open [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173) and start using the app.

> The frontend is configured to proxy `/api` requests to `http://localhost:3001` (see `frontend/vite.config.js`).

